  Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon A\to B]]></fr:tex> be a surjection.
  Consider the family <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F := {\mathopen {}\{f^{-1}(b)\colon b \in  B\}\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.
  Note that this is a family of non-empty sets since <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is a surjection.
  Then AC gives a choice function <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[c\colon F\to \bigcup  F]]></fr:tex>.
  Note that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\bigcup  F = A]]></fr:tex>.
  Then we define <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[i\colon B\to A]]></fr:tex> by <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[i(b) := c(f^{-1}(b))]]></fr:tex>.
  It is routine to verify that it is the required injection.
